# seamless analysis...

# CLEAN UP FUNCTIONS:
    
    # 1. make sure 'inactive' is not null
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""update seamless set inactive = false where inactive is null""")
    
    # 2. mark any entries without links updated as 'updated' if upd_vend_content is not null
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""
    update seamless
    set upd_search_links = upd_vend_content
    where 
    (upd_search_links is null and upd_vend_content is not null)
    or
    (upd_search_links < upd_vend_content);
""")   

    # 3. update seamless inactive from seamless_closed
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""
    update seamless s
    set inactive = true
    from seamless_closed sc
    where s.sl_link = sc.sl_link
    and sc.inactive is true;
""")
    
    # 4. delete from seamless_closed where updated seamless
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""
update seamless_closed sc
set vend_name = null
from seamless s
where s.sl_link = sc.sl_link
and sc.upd_seamless is true;

delete from seamless_closed sc
where vend_name is null;
""")

    # 5. remove entries outside of Manhattan

# conn.set_isolation_level(0)
# cur.execute(delete_cmd)

cmd = """
select s.* from seamless s, (select array_agg(B::integer) A from unnest(array%(mn_zipcodes)s) B) as f1 
where not array[s.zipcode] && A order by s.zipcode;"""%{'mn_zipcodes':mn_zipcodes}
test = pd.read_sql(cmd,engine)
if len(test)>0:
    print """Really delete out-of-area rows?\n
             Use This:\n\n
             conn.set_isolation_level(0)
             cur.execute(delete_cmd)\n"""
    delete_cmd = """
        delete from seamless s
        using (select array_agg(B::integer) A from unnest(array%(mn_zipcodes)s) B) as f1 
        where not array[s.zipcode] && A;"""%{'mn_zipcodes':mn_zipcodes}
    raise SystemError()
    
    
print 'DB -- seamless'
d = pd.DataFrame(columns=['Value','Var'])

sl = pd.read_sql('select * from seamless',engine)
sl_all_vend = len(sl)

sl_link_updates = sl[sl.upd_search_links.map(lambda s: True if s!=None else False)==True].sort('upd_search_links',ascending=True).upd_search_links.tolist()
oldest_sl_link_update,newest_sl_link_update = sl_link_updates[0],sl_link_updates[-1]
sl_null_link_updates = sl_all_vend - len(sl_link_updates)

sl_content_updates = sl[sl.upd_vend_content.map(lambda s: True if s!=None else False)==True].sort('upd_vend_content',ascending=True).upd_vend_content.tolist()
oldest_sl_content_update,newest_sl_content_update = sl_content_updates[0],sl_content_updates[-1]
sl_null_content_updates = sl_all_vend - len(sl_content_updates)

sl_not_updated = (sl_all_vend-(sl_null_link_updates+sl_null_content_updates))
sl_perc_updated = str(round(100 * (float(sl_not_updated)/float(sl_all_vend)),2))+' %'


sl_updated = sl[(sl.upd_search_links.map(lambda s: True if s!=None else False)==True) & 
                (sl.upd_vend_content.map(lambda s: True if s!=None else False)==True)].copy().reset_index(drop=True)

sl_all_upd_vend = len(sl_updated)
sl_uniq_vend = len(sl_updated.vend_id.unique().tolist())

sl_active_vend = len(sl_updated[sl_updated.inactive==False])
sl_inactive_vend = len(sl_updated[sl_updated.inactive==True])
sl_perc_active_vend= str(round(100 * (float(sl_active_vend)/float(sl_all_upd_vend)),2))+' %'

sl_with_geom = len(sl_updated[sl_updated.geom.isnull()==False])
sl_WITHOUT_geom = sl_all_upd_vend - sl_with_geom
sl_perc_with_geom = str(round(100 * (float(sl_with_geom)/float(sl_all_upd_vend)),2))+' %'

sl_with_matched_bbl = sl_updated.bbl.map(lambda s: True if str(s).lower()!='nan' else False).tolist().count(True)
sl_perc_with_matched_bbl = str(round(100 * (float(sl_with_matched_bbl)/float(sl_all_upd_vend)),2))+' %'
sl_WITHOUT_matched_bbl = sl_all_upd_vend - sl_with_matched_bbl


params = [
    ('Oldest SL Link Update',oldest_sl_link_update),
    ('Newest SL Link Update',newest_sl_link_update),
    ('Oldest SL Vend Content Update',oldest_sl_content_update),
    ('Newest SL Vend Content Update',newest_sl_content_update),
    ('# of Seamless Vendors',sl_all_vend),
    ('# of Duplicate VEND Rows',len(sl_updated) - sl_uniq_vend),
    ('% of Updated Seamless Vendors ("VEND")',sl_perc_updated),
    ('# of VEND without Links Updated',sl_null_link_updates),
    ('# of VEND without Content Updated',sl_null_content_updates),
    ('% of Active Seamless VEND',sl_perc_active_vend),
    ('# of Inactive Seamless VEND',sl_inactive_vend),
    ('% of VEND with geom',sl_perc_with_geom),
    ('# WITHOUT geom',sl_WITHOUT_geom),
    ('% of VEND with BBL',sl_perc_with_matched_bbl),
    ('# WITHOUT BBL',sl_WITHOUT_matched_bbl),
         ]

for it in params:
    d = d.append({'Var':it[0],'Value':it[1]},ignore_index=True)
print d

# seamless_closed analysis
print 'DB -- seamless_closed'
d = pd.DataFrame(columns=['Value','Var'])

d = d.append({'Var':'# of Potential Active Vendors to Scrape',
              'Value':pd.read_sql(""" 
                                    select count(*) u from seamless_closed sc
                                    where inactive is False
                                    and upd_seamless is false
                                    """,engine).u[0]},
            ignore_index=True)

d = d.append({'Var':'# of Potential Vendors Matched to seamless DB',
              'Value':pd.read_sql(""" 
                                    select count(*) u from seamless_closed sc
                                    inner join seamless s
                                    on s.sl_link ilike sc.sl_link
                                    """,engine).u[0]},
            ignore_index=True)

d = d.append({'Var':'(above) NOT Matched to seamless DB',
              'Value':pd.read_sql(""" 
                                    select count(*) u from seamless_closed sc
                                    where not exists 
                                        (select * from seamless s 
                                        where s.sl_link = sc.sl_link)
                                    and inactive is False
                                    """,engine).u[0]},
            ignore_index=True)

print d

# yelp

## CLEANUP FUNCTIONS:

# 1. remove entries outside of Manhattan
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute('drop table if exists tmp;')
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""
    create table tmp as
    select 
        s.*,
        True::boolean non_mn_zipcode
    from 
        yelp s, 
        (select array_agg(B::bigint) A from unnest(array%(mn_zipcodes)s) B) as f1 
    where not array[s.postal_code] && A order by s.postal_code;

    delete from yelp y
    using tmp t
    where t.gid = y.gid;

    with upd as (
        update yelp_geom_error y
        set
            id = y.id,
            vend_name = y.vend_name,
            phone = y.phone,
            address = y.address,
            city = y.city,
            state_code = y.state_code,
            postal_code = y.postal_code,
            display_phone = y.display_phone,
            is_claimed = y.is_claimed,
            is_closed = y.is_closed,
            menu_date_updated = y.menu_date_updated,
            menu_provider = y.menu_provider,
            rating = y.rating,
            review_count = y.review_count,
            categories = y.categories,
            url = y.url,
            latitude = y.latitude,
            longitude = y.longitude,
            geo_accuracy = y.geo_accuracy,
            hours = y.hours,
            hours_updated = y.hours_updated,
            extra_info = y.extra_info,

y_a_WITHOUT_online_ordering = y_a_vend_cnt - y_a_with_online_ordering
y_a_perc_online_ordering = str(round(100 * (float(y_a_with_online_ordering)/float(y_a_vend_cnt)),2))+' %'

### yelp: remove unlikely matches by comparing matched/added geoms w/ yelp-provided coord.s
cmd="""

drop table if exists tmp;

create table tmp as
    SELECT 
        y.id compare_id,
        y.vend_name vend_name,
        y.address address,
        0.0::double precision seperation_dist,
        ST_SetSRID(ST_Point(y.longitude, y.latitude),4326)::geometry(Point,4326) geom
    FROM yelp y
    WHERE geom is not null;

update tmp set seperation_dist = null;

update tmp A 
    set seperation_dist = ST_Distance_Spheroid(A.geom,B.geom,
                                'SPHEROID["WGS 84",6378137,298.257223563]') 
    from yelp B 
    where 
        A.compare_id = B.id
        and A.geom is not null
        and B.geom is not null;

"""
%sql postgres@routing $cmd

### yelp: compare matched added geoms w/ yelp-provided coord.s
cmd="""

drop table if exists tmp;

create table tmp as
    SELECT 
        y.id compare_id,
        y.vend_name vend_name,
        y.address address,
        0.0::double precision seperation_dist,
        ST_SetSRID(ST_Point(y.longitude, y.latitude),4326)::geometry(Point,4326) geom
    FROM yelp y
    WHERE geom is not null;

update tmp set seperation_dist = null;

update tmp A 
    set seperation_dist = ST_Distance_Spheroid(A.geom,B.geom,
                                'SPHEROID["WGS 84",6378137,298.257223563]') 
    from yelp B 
    where 
        A.compare_id = B.id
        and A.geom is not null
        and B.geom is not null;

update tmp set geom=null where seperation_dist>400.0;

update yelp y set geom=null
from tmp t
where t.geom is null and y.id=t.compare_id;

drop table tmp;

"""
%sql postgres@routing $cmd

def match_distinct_mnv_var(tbl='seamless',tbl_id='vend_id',vend_name='vend_name',match_var='vend_name'):
    """
    Matches distinct $tbl variables with distinct mn_vendor vars.
    
    Usages:
    
        match_distinct_mnv_var(tbl='yelp',tbl_id='id',vend_name='vend_name',match_var='phone')
        match_distinct_mnv_var(tbl='seamless',tbl_id='vend_id',vend_name='vend_name',match_var='vend_name')
        match_distinct_mnv_var(tbl='yelp',tbl_id='id',vend_name='vend_name',match_var='address')
    
    """
    T = {'tbl':tbl,
         'tbl_id':tbl_id,
         'vend_name':vend_name,
         'match_var':match_var}
    
    x = pd.read_sql("select * from %(tbl)s"%T,engine)

    x_var_tot = x[match_var].tolist()
    x[match_var+'_cnt'] = x[match_var].map(lambda i: x_var_tot.count(i))
    x_var_id_dict = dict(zip(x[x[match_var+'_cnt']==1][match_var].tolist(),x[x[match_var+'_cnt']==1][tbl_id].tolist()))
    x_var_id_dict_keys = x_var_id_dict.keys()

    mnv  = pd.read_sql("select * from mnv where %(tbl)s_id is null"%T,engine)
    mnv_var_tot = mnv[match_var].tolist()
    mnv[match_var+'_cnt'] = mnv[match_var].map(lambda i: mnv_var_tot.count(i))
    mnv_x = mnv[ (mnv[match_var].isin(x_var_id_dict_keys)==True)&(mnv[match_var+'_cnt']==1) ].copy()
    mnv_x['%(tbl)s_id'%T] = mnv_x[match_var].map(x_var_id_dict)

    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute( """drop table if exists tmp;""")
    mnv_x.to_sql('tmp',engine)
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute("""
        alter table tmp add column tid serial primary key;
        update tmp set tid = nextval(pg_get_serial_sequence('tmp','tid'));
    """)
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute("""
        update mnv m
        set %(tbl)s_id = t.%(tbl)s_id
        from tmp t
        where m.camis = t.camis;

        drop table tmp;
    """%T)

### __ create/update '*_geom_error' tables for remainders of yelp,seamless,mnv

tables = ['yelp','seamless']
id_cols = {'yelp':'id','seamless':'vend_id'}

c="""
    select table_name tbl from information_schema.tables 
    WHERE table_schema='public'
    and table_name = ANY(array%s)
    """%str(map(lambda s: s+'_geom_error',tables))
chk = pd.read_sql(c,engine).tbl.tolist()

for tbl in tables:
    T = {'base_tbl':tbl,'err_tbl':tbl+'_geom_error','id_col':id_cols[tbl]}
    if chk.count(T['err_tbl'])==0:
        c="""
            create table %(err_tbl)s as
                select * from %(base_tbl)s where geom is null;
                
            delete from %(base_tbl)s t 
                using (select array_agg(t2.%(id_col)s) A from %(err_tbl)s t2) 
                where y.%(id_col)s = any(A);
            """%T
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute(c)
    else:
        cols = pd.read_sql("""   
            select column_name cols 
            from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS 
            where table_name = '%(base_tbl)s'"""%T,engine).cols.map(str).tolist()

        T.update({'upd_defs'   : '\n'.join(map(lambda s: s+' = t.'+s+',',cols))[:-1],
                  'insert_cols': ','.join(cols) })
        T.update({'select_cols': ','.join(map(lambda s: 't.'+s,cols))})
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        c="""
            with upd as (
                update %(err_tbl)s s
                set %(upd_defs)s
                from %(base_tbl)s t
                where s.%(id_col)s = t.%(id_col)s
                and t.geom is null
                returning s.%(id_col)s %(id_col)s
                        )                   
            insert into %(err_tbl)s ( %(insert_cols)s )

            select %(select_cols)s
                from 
                    %(base_tbl)s t,
                    (select array_agg(t2.%(id_col)s) A from %(err_tbl)s t2) as f2
                where (not A @> array[t.%(id_col)s])
                and t.geom is null;

            delete from %(base_tbl)s t 
                using (select array_agg(t2.%(id_col)s) A from %(err_tbl)s t2) as f1
                where t.%(id_col)s = any(A);
            """%T
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute(c)

### __ create 'all_info' from { mn_vendor,seamless,yelp } [ about 2.5 min ] 

import sys
reload(sys)
sys.setdefaultencoding('UTF8')

def remove_all_NaN(tbl):
    
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    d=pd.read_sql(""" select column_name cols
                      from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS 
                      where table_name = '%s'"""%tbl,engine).cols.tolist()

    for it in d:
        T = {'tbl':tbl,'col':it}
        cmd=""" update %(tbl)s set %(col)s = null
                where (
                    %(col)s::text='NaN' 
                    or %(col)s::text='None'
                    or %(col)s::text ilike 'nan'
                    or %(col)s::text ilike 'nat') """%T
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute(cmd)
        if (it.find('phone')!=-1 and it.find('display')==-1):
            cmd=""" update %(tbl)s set %(col)s = null
            where %(col)s = 0 """%T
            conn.set_isolation_level(0)
            cur.execute(cmd)
    return

def rename_all_cols_with_label(tbl,prefix='',exceptions=[]):
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    d=pd.read_sql(""" select column_name cols
                      from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS 
                      where table_name = '%s'"""%tbl,engine).cols.tolist()
    base_cmd,s='ALTER TABLE %s '%tbl,''
    for it in d:
        if exceptions.count(it)==0:
            s+=base_cmd+'rename column %(col)s to %(pre)s%(col)s;\n'%{'col':it,'pre':prefix}
    s = s.rstrip(' ,')+';'
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute(s)
    return

def delete_pts_outside_mn():
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute("""
        delete from all_info v
        using
            (
                SELECT ST_Buffer(  ST_ConcaveHull(  (ST_Collect(f.the_geom)), 100, false  ),.0005) mn 
                FROM ( 
                SELECT *, (ST_Dump(geom)).geom As the_geom 
                FROM pluto
                ) As f
            ) as f2
        where not st_containsproperly(mn,v.geom);
    """)
    return

conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("drop table if exists all_info")

# 
# CAREFUL with the 'c1' & 'c2' below... the sequence order [ mn_vendors,seamless,yelp ] is essential #
# 

c1 = """
    select *
    from 
        (select * from mnv mn) as f1
    left join seamless sl on f1.seamless_id=sl.vend_id
    right join yelp y on f1.yelp_id=y.id
    """
grp = pd.read_sql(c1,engine)
grp_cols = grp.columns.tolist()

# ---- horizontally split up results with column cnt and rename
c2 = """   
    select mn_cnt,y_cnt,sl_cnt
    from
        (select count(*) mn_cnt from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS where table_name = 'mnv') as f1,
        (select count(*) sl_cnt from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS where table_name = 'seamless') as f2,
        (select count(*) y_cnt from INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS where table_name = 'yelp') as f3
    """
t=pd.read_sql(c2,engine)
t_cols=t.columns.tolist()

cnt_dict=dict(zip(t.columns.tolist(),t.ix[0,:].tolist()))
tbl_dict={'mn':'mnv','sl':'seamless','y':'yelp'}

new_grp_cols,pt=[],0
for cnt in sorted(cnt_dict.keys()):
    tbl_key = cnt[:cnt.find('_cnt')+1]
    next_pt = pt+cnt_dict[cnt]
    for i in range(pt,next_pt):
        new_grp_cols.append( tbl_key + str(grp_cols[i]) )
    pt = next_pt

len(new_grp_cols) == sum(cnt_dict.values())
grp.columns = [new_grp_cols]

# ---- clean up
take_cols = ['mn_camis','sl_vend_id','y_gid','mn_vend_name','sl_vend_name','y_vend_name',
             'mn_address','sl_address','y_display_address','y_neighborhoods','mn_zipcode',
             'sl_zipcode','y_postal_code','mn_phone','sl_phone','y_display_phone',
             'sl_sl_link','y_url','y_website','y_menu_page','y_menu_date_updated','y_menu_provider',
             'sl_inactive','y_is_claimed','y_is_closed','y_online_ordering','y_extra_info','y_hours',
             'mn_cuisinecode','sl_cuisine','y_categories','sl_description',
             'sl_price','y_price_range','sl_deliv_min','sl_deliv_fee','sl_perc_fee','sl_pickup_est','sl_deliv_est',
             'sl_rating','sl_rating_total','sl_rating_perc','y_rating','y_review_count','sl_reviews',
             'mn_inspdate','sl_upd_search_links','sl_upd_vend_content','y_last_api_update','y_hours_updated']
grp = grp.ix[:,take_cols]
take_cols_with_geom = take_cols + ['geom']

re_encode_cols = ['mn_vend_name','sl_vend_name','y_vend_name',
                  'sl_description']
for it in re_encode_cols:
    grp[it] = grp[it].map(lambda s: s if type(s)==NoneType else codecs.encode(s,'utf8','ignore'))

phone_cols = ['mn_phone','sl_phone']
for it in phone_cols:
    grp[it] = grp[it].map(lambda s: 0 if s.is_integer()==False else int(s))

title_cols = ['mn_vend_name','sl_vend_name','y_vend_name',
              'mn_address','sl_address','y_display_address']
for it in title_cols:
    grp[it] = grp[it].map(lambda s: str(s).title())

datetime_cols = ['mn_inspdate','sl_upd_search_links','sl_upd_vend_content','y_last_api_update',
                 'y_menu_date_updated','y_hours_updated']
for it in datetime_cols:
    grp[it] = grp[it].map(str)

# ---- push to pgSQL
grp['y_hours'] = grp.y_hours.map(lambda s: None if (str(s)=='nan' or str(s)=='None') else '\n'.join([it[0]+': '+it[1] for it in eval(str(s))]) )
grp['y_extra_info'] = grp.y_extra_info.map(lambda s: None if (str(s)=='nan' or str(s)=='None') else '\n'.join([it[0]+': '+it[1] for it in eval(str(s))]) )
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute( """drop table if exists all_info;""")
grp.to_sql('all_info',engine)
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""
    alter table all_info add column glob_id serial primary key;
    update all_info set glob_id = nextval(pg_get_serial_sequence('all_info','glob_id'));
    """)

# ---- make first part of DB
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""
    ALTER TABLE all_info 
        drop column index;

    ALTER TABLE all_info 
        add column lat double precision,
        add column lon double precision,
        add column geom geometry(Point,4326),
        add column new_notes text,
        add column follow_up text,
        add column old_notes text,
        add column mark_for_edit text;

    UPDATE all_info c set geom = t_geom
    from (select t.camis t_id,t.geom t_geom from mnv t where geom is not null) as f1
    where c.mn_camis = t_id
    and (c.mn_camis is not null and ( not c.mn_camis::text ilike 'nan' ) );

    UPDATE all_info c set geom = t_geom
    from (select t.gid t_id,t.geom t_geom from yelp t where geom is not null) as f1
    where c.y_gid = t_id
    and (c.y_gid is not null and ( not c.y_gid::text ilike 'nan' ) );

    UPDATE all_info c set geom = t_geom
    from (select t.vend_id t_id,t.geom t_geom from seamless t where geom is not null) as f1
    where c.sl_vend_id = t_id
    and (c.sl_vend_id is not null and ( not c.sl_vend_id::text ilike 'nan' ) );
    """)

# ---- account for all mnv records
uniq_grp_mn_ids = grp[grp.mn_camis.isnull()==False].mn_camis.unique().tolist()
all_mn_ids = pd.read_sql("""
    select distinct camis from mnv 
    where geom is not null
    and (
        camis is not null 
        and ( not camis::text ilike 'nan' )
        and ( not camis::text ilike 'nat' ) 
        )
    """,engine)

### All_vend.csv to gDrive
T = {'base_file_path':'/Users/admin/gDrive/Aporo/marketing/all_info',
     'file_ext':'.csv'}
map_groups = pd.read_sql('select distinct map_group from all_info',engine).map_group.tolist()
drop_cols = ['geom','sl_upd_search_links','mn_cuisinecode',
                 'mn_zipcode','sl_zipcode','y_postal_code',
                 'y_last_api_update','sl_rating_perc','map_group']
for m_grp in map_groups:
    T.update({'m_grp':m_grp})
    grp_cnt = pd.read_sql('select count(*) c from all_info where map_group = %(m_grp)s'%T,engine).c[0]
    if grp_cnt<=2000:
        grp = pd.read_sql("""
                select * from all_info
                where map_group = %(m_grp)s 
                order by glob_id asc"""%T,engine)
        grp = grp.drop(drop_cols,axis=1)
        f_path = T['base_file_path'] + '_grp_%(m_grp)s'%T + T['file_ext']
        grp.to_csv(f_path,index=False,encoding='utf-8')
    else:
        grp_size = 2000
        grp_num = int(2 + float(grp_cnt)//float(grp_size))
        offset = 0
        z=[]
        T.update({'limit':grp_size,
                  'offset':offset})
        for i in range(grp_num):
            grp = pd.read_sql("""
                select * from all_info 
                where map_group = %(m_grp)s
                order by glob_id desc 
                limit %(limit)s offset %(offset)s
                              """%T,engine)
            z.append(len(grp))
            T.update({'offset':i*grp_size})
            grp = grp.drop(drop_cols,axis=1)
            f_path = T['base_file_path'] + '_grp_%(m_grp)s_'%T + str(i) + T['file_ext']
            if os_path.isfile(f_path):
                os_cmd('rm '+f_path)
            grp.to_csv(f_path,index=False,encoding='utf-8')

# Divide Data by Geolocation

import geopandas as gd
%matplotlib inline

def perpendicular_degrees_from_degrees(st_deg,sorted_clockwise='always'):
    pos = st_deg + 90
    if pos>360: pos = pos - 360
    neg = st_deg - 90
    if neg<0:   neg = 360 + neg
    a,b = sorted([pos,neg])
    return a,b

show_info=True
min_v,max_v = 1900.0,2000.0
street_to_divide_by = ''
T={}

# divide by points
bot_pt = (40.699857,-74.025184)
top_pt = (40.88103,-73.89526)

# divide-by-street       NOT FULLY SETUP YET (2014.11.22)
# street_to_divide_by = 42

# ---------------------
# ---------------------


# set all map_group to null
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""
    update all_info v
    set map_group = null
    """)

# [ divide-by-street ] get angles
if street_to_divide_by != '':
    c=  """
        SELECT 
            (ST_Y(s_pt), ST_X(s_pt)) s_pts,
            (ST_Y(e_pt), ST_X(e_pt)) e_pts,
            degrees( ST_Azimuth(s_pt,e_pt) ) degrees,
            g
        FROM
            (
            SELECT 
                ST_StartPoint(geom) s_pt,
                ST_EndPoint(geom) e_pt,
                geom g
            FROM 
                address_idx 
            WHERE geom is not null and street ilike '%s%s'
                ) as f1
        """%(street_to_divide_by,'%%')

    g = gd.read_postgis(c,conn,'g')

    st_start_coords = dict(zip(['lon','lat'],g.s_pts[0].strip('()').split(',')))
    st_end_coords = dict(zip(['lon','lat'],g.e_pts[0].strip('()').split(',')))
    T.update({'st_start_coords':"SELECT ST_GeomFromText('POINT(%(lat)s %(lon)s)',4326) t_l_pt"%st_start_coords,
              'st_end_coords':"SELECT ST_GeomFromText('POINT(%(lat)s %(lon)s)',4326) t_r_pt"%st_end_coords})

    st_angle = g.degrees[0]
    u_angle,d_angle = perpendicular_degrees_from_degrees(st_angle)
    r_angle,l_angle = perpendicular_degrees_from_degrees(u_angle)
    T.update({'l_angle':l_angle,'r_angle':r_angle,
              'd_angle':d_angle,'u_angle':u_angle})

    # Using angle, find approximate lines on each side where line doesn't touch MN

# make Manhattan geoms and start geom collection
base_geom = []
MN ="""
    SELECT 
        ST_AsEWKT( mn_geom ) mn_geom,
        ST_AsEWKT( mn_e ) mn_e
    FROM (
        SELECT mn_geom,ST_Envelope(mn_geom) mn_e
        FROM (
            SELECT ST_Buffer(  ST_ConcaveHull(  (ST_Collect(f.the_geom)), 100, false  ), 
                               .0005) as mn_geom 
            FROM ( SELECT *, (ST_Dump(geom)).geom As the_geom 
            FROM pluto) As f
            ) as f1
        ) as f2;
    """
p = pd.read_sql(MN,conn)

mn_geom="ST_GeomFromText('%s',4326) geom"%p.mn_geom[0].split(';')[1]
base_geom.extend(gd.read_postgis('select %s'%mn_geom,conn).geom)
if street_to_divide_by != '':
    mn_e="ST_GeomFromText('%s',4326) geom"%p.mn_e[0].split(';')[1]
    base_geom.extend(gd.read_postgis('select %s'%mn_e,conn).geom)

    outer_box = pd.read_sql('select box2d(%s) b;'%mn_e_b.replace('geom',''),conn)
    a_b_l,a_t_r = outer_box.b[0].strip('BOX()').split(',') # absolute bottom left, etc...
    a_b_l,a_t_r = a_b_l.split(' '),a_t_r.split(' ')


# make points (bot_pt,top_pt) at each end of MN
bot_pt_pg = "SELECT ST_GeomFromText('POINT(%s %s)',4326) bot_pt"%(str(bot_pt[1]),str(bot_pt[0]))
top_pt_pg = "SELECT ST_GeomFromText('POINT(%s %s)',4326) top_pt"%(str(top_pt[1]),str(top_pt[0]))
base_geom.extend(gd.read_postgis(bot_pt_pg,conn,'bot_pt').bot_pt)
base_geom.extend(gd.read_postgis(top_pt_pg,conn,'top_pt').top_pt)


# make line (k_line) connecting points
T = {'bot_pt':bot_pt_pg,'top_pt':top_pt_pg}
c="""
    select ST_MakeLine(bot_pt,top_pt) k_line
    from
        (%(bot_pt)s) as f1,
        (%(top_pt)s) as f2
    """%T
base_geom.extend(gd.read_postgis(c,conn,'k_line').k_line)


# get length (k_line_len) of k_line (google says 12.9 miles)
feet_per_meter = 3.28084
miles_per_foot = 0.000189394
miles_per_meter = 0.000621371
T.update({'m_to_ft':feet_per_meter,'ft_to_mi':miles_per_foot,'m_to_mi':miles_per_meter})

c="""
    select ( %(m_to_mi)s * ST_Distance_Sphere(bot_pt,top_pt) ) distance_in_miles
    from
        (%(bot_pt)s) as f1,
        (%(top_pt)s) as f2
    """%T
k_line_len = pd.read_sql(c,engine).distance_in_miles[0]

proj_lat_dist = (k_line_len / 5.0) * ( 1 / T['m_to_mi'] )
proj_lon_dist = (k_line_len / 10.0) * ( 1 / T['m_to_mi'] )
T.update({'proj_lat_dist':proj_lat_dist,
          'proj_lon_dist':proj_lon_dist})


# get azimuth angle (k_line_angle) of connecting line
c="""
    select degrees( ST_Azimuth(bot_pt,top_pt) ) degrees
    from
        (%(bot_pt)s) as f1,
        (%(top_pt)s) as f2
    """%T
k_line_angle = pd.read_sql(c,engine).degrees[0]


# get angles (l_angle,r_angle) for perpendicular lines on left and right
r_angle,l_angle = perpendicular_degrees_from_degrees(k_line_angle)
u_angle,d_angle = perpendicular_degrees_from_degrees(l_angle)
T.update({'l_angle':l_angle,'r_angle':r_angle,
          'd_angle':d_angle,'u_angle':u_angle})


# get base points by projecting perpendicular at bottom of k_line
c="""
    select 
        ST_MakeLine(l_pt,r_pt) new_line,
        (ST_Y(l_pt), ST_X(l_pt)) l_pt,
        (ST_Y(r_pt), ST_X(r_pt)) r_pt
    from
        (
        select 
            ST_Project(bot_pt,%(proj_lat_dist)s,radians(%(l_angle)s))::geometry(Point,4326) l_pt,
            ST_Project(bot_pt,%(proj_lat_dist)s,radians(%(r_angle)s))::geometry(Point,4326) r_pt
        from
            (%(bot_pt)s) as f1
        ) as f3
    """%T
g = gd.read_postgis(c,conn,'new_line')
l_coords = dict(zip(['lon','lat'],g.l_pt[0].strip('()').split(',')))
r_coords = dict(zip(['lon','lat'],g.r_pt[0].strip('()').split(',')))
T.update({'b_l_pt':"SELECT ST_GeomFromText('POINT(%(lat)s %(lon)s)',4326) b_l_pt"%l_coords,
          'b_r_pt':"SELECT ST_GeomFromText('POINT(%(lat)s %(lon)s)',4326) b_r_pt"%r_coords})
def get_point_cnt(T,geoms=[]):
    geoms=[]

    ## print '\n\n THIS IS NOT CHECKING FOR POINTS BELOW STARTING POINT. \n\n'

    # project points perpendicular line (T_line) up k_line
    c="""
        select 
            ST_MakeLine(t_l_pt,t_r_pt) new_line,
            (ST_Y(t_l_pt), ST_X(t_l_pt)) t_l_pt,
            (ST_Y(t_r_pt), ST_X(t_r_pt)) t_r_pt
        from
            (
            select 
                ST_Project(b_l_pt,%(proj_lon_dist)s,radians(%(u_angle)s))::geometry(Point,4326) t_l_pt,
                ST_Project(b_r_pt,%(proj_lon_dist)s,radians(%(u_angle)s))::geometry(Point,4326) t_r_pt
            from
                (%(b_l_pt)s) as f1,
                (%(b_r_pt)s) as f2
            ) as f3
        """%T
    g = gd.read_postgis(c,conn,'new_line')
    l_coords = dict(zip(['lon','lat'],g.t_l_pt[0].strip('()').split(',')))
    r_coords = dict(zip(['lon','lat'],g.t_r_pt[0].strip('()').split(',')))
    T.update({'t_l_pt':"SELECT ST_GeomFromText('POINT(%(lat)s %(lon)s)',4326) t_l_pt"%l_coords,
              't_r_pt':"SELECT ST_GeomFromText('POINT(%(lat)s %(lon)s)',4326) t_r_pt"%r_coords})

    # make box with points from two lines
    c="""
        SELECT 
            ST_ConcaveHull( ST_LineFromMultiPoint( ST_Collect( array[t_l_pt,t_r_pt,b_l_pt,b_r_pt] ) ),
                            100,False) box               
        FROM
            (%(t_l_pt)s) as f1,
            (%(t_r_pt)s) as f2,
            (%(b_l_pt)s) as f3,
            (%(b_r_pt)s) as f4    
        """%T
    g = gd.read_postgis(c,conn,'box')
    geoms.extend(g.box)
    
    # check if any points in box
    c="""
        SELECT count(*) cnt
        FROM 
            all_info v,
            (
                SELECT 
                    ST_ConcaveHull( ST_LineFromMultiPoint( ST_Collect( array[t_l_pt,t_r_pt,b_l_pt,b_r_pt] ) ),
                                    100,False) box               
                FROM
                    (%(t_l_pt)s) as f1,
                    (%(t_r_pt)s) as f2,
                    (%(b_l_pt)s) as f3,
                    (%(b_r_pt)s) as f4
            ) as f5
        WHERE ST_ContainsProperly(box,v.geom);
        """%T
    cnt = pd.read_sql(c,conn).cnt[0]
    
    return cnt,T,geoms

# final iteration
def update_map_groups(min_v=1800.0,max_v=2000.0,
                      base_geom=[],show_info=False):
    min_v,max_v = float(min_v),float(max_v)
    box_num,saved_boxes,last_move = 0,[],'start'
    while last_move!='complete':
        if show_info==True: print box_num,'\t\t box_num'
        cnt = 0
        incr_seg,last_cnt = 0,0
        while not (min_v<=cnt<=max_v):
            cnt,T_tmp,box = get_point_cnt(T)
            if cnt<min_v:
                if (last_move=='increase') and (cnt==last_cnt): 
                    last_move = 'complete'
                    break
                else:
                    incr_seg = (min_v-cnt)/min_v
                    T.update({'proj_lon_dist':T['proj_lon_dist']+(incr_seg*T['proj_lon_dist'])})
                    last_move = 'increase'
                    last_cnt = cnt

            elif cnt>max_v:
                if incr_seg==0:  decr_seg = 0.5
                else: 
                    decr_seg = .5 * incr_seg
                    incr_seg = decr_seg
                T.update({'proj_lon_dist':T['proj_lon_dist']-(decr_seg*T['proj_lon_dist'])})
                last_move = 'decrease'
            if show_info==True: 
                if not (min_v<=cnt<=max_v):
                    print cnt,'\t\t Last Count'
                else:
                    print cnt,'\t\t Save Count'


        saved_boxes.extend(box)

        box_txt = "ST_GeomFromText('%s',4326)"%box[0].to_wkt()
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute("""
            update all_info v
            set map_group = %s
            from %s box
            where ST_ContainsProperly(box,v.geom)
            """%(str(box_num),box_txt))

        T.update({ 'b_l_pt':T_tmp['t_l_pt'].replace('t_l_pt','b_l_pt'),
                   'b_r_pt':T_tmp['t_r_pt'].replace('t_r_pt','b_r_pt'),
                   't_l_pt':T_tmp['t_l_pt'],'t_r_pt':T_tmp['t_r_pt'],})

        box_num += 1

        if last_move=='complete':
            break

    if show_info==True: gd.GeoSeries(base_geom+saved_boxes).plot()
    
    return saved_boxes

saved_geom = update_map_groups(min_v=1800.0,max_v=2000.0,
                               base_geom=base_geom,show_info=True)
gd.GeoSeries(base_geom+saved_geom).plot()

# seamless f(x)s
def update_pgsql_with_seamless_page_content(br):
    html = codecs.encode(br.source(),'utf8','ignore')
    seamless_link = br.get_url()
    if seamless_link.find('http')!=0: seamless_link='http://www.seamless.com/food-delivery/'+seamless_link
    vendor_id = int(seamless_link[seamless_link[:-2].rfind('.')+1:-2])
    
    t = getTagsByAttr(html, 'span', {'id':'VendorName'},contents=False)
    if len(t)==0:
        try:
            a = getTagsByAttr(html, 'div', {'id':'Bummer'},contents=False)
            b = a[0].text.replace('\n','').replace('Bummer!','').strip()
            vend_name = b[:b.find('(')].strip()
            addr = re_findall(r'[(](.*)[)]',b)[0]
            T = {'vendor_id':vendor_id,'vend_name':vend_name,'addr':addr}
            cmd =   """
                    update seamless 
                    set 
                        inactive = true,
                        vend_name = %(vend_name)s,
                        address = %(addr)s,
                        upd_vend_content = 'now'::timestamp with time zone
                    where vend_id = %(vendor_id)s
                    """%T
        except:
            T = {'vendor_id':vendor_id}
            cmd =   """
                    update seamless 
                    set 
                        inactive = true,
                        upd_vend_content = 'now'::timestamp with time zone
                    where vend_id = %(vendor_id)s
                    """%T
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute(cmd)
    else:
        vend_name = t[0].getText().replace('\n','').strip()

    addr = getTagsByAttr(html, 'span', {'itemprop':'streetAddress'},contents=False)[0].contents[0]
    addr = addr[:addr.find('(')].strip()
    z = getTagsByAttr(html, 'span', {'itemprop':'postalCode'},contents=False)[0].contents[0]

    if z.find('-')!=-1:
        zipcode = int(z[:z.find('-')])
    else:
        zipcode = int(z)
    p = getTagsByAttr(html, 'span', {'itemprop':'telephone'},contents=False)[0].contents[0]
    excl_chars = ['(',')','-','x','/',',',' ']
    for it in excl_chars: p = p.replace(it,'')
    phone = int(p.strip()[:10])
    if len(str(phone))!=10:
        beep()
        raise SystemError()
    try:
        price = int(getTagsByAttr(html, 'span', {'class':'price-text'},contents=False)[0].getText().count('$'))
    except:
        price = -1
    try:
        rating = int(getTagsByAttr(html, 'a', {'class':'user-rating'},contents=False)[0].img.attrs['alt'].split(' ')[0])
        rating_total = int(getTagsByAttr(html, 'span', {'itemprop':'ratingCount',
                                          'id':'TotalRatings'},contents=False)[0].getText().replace('ratings','').strip())
        rating_perc = rating_total/rating
        reviews = int(getTagsByAttr(html, 'span', {'itemprop':'reviewCount',
                                                 'id':'TotalReviews'},contents=False)[0].getText())
    except:
        rating = rating_total = rating_perc = -1
        reviews = 0
    v = html.find('Delivery Estimate:')
    deliv_est = '-'.join(re_findall(r'\d+', html[v:v+len('Delivery Estimate:')+100] ))
    v = html.find('Delivery Minimum:')
    deliv_min = float('.'.join(re_findall(r'\d+', html[v:v+len('Delivery Minimum:')+100] )[:2]))
    pickup_est = '-'.join(re_findall(r'\d+', getTagsByAttr(html, 'span', {'class':'ready-time'},contents=False)[0].getText()))
    v = getTagsByAttr(html, 'div', {'class':'estimates',
                         'id':'RestaurantDetails'},contents=False)[0]
    estimates_blob = re_sub(r'\s+', ' ', v.findAll('span')[3].getText().replace('\n',''))
    description = getTagsByAttr(html, 'meta', {'property':'og:description'},contents=False)[0].attrs['content']
    try:
        cuisine = getTagsByAttr(html, 'li', {'itemprop':'servesCuisine'},contents=False)[0].contents[0]
    except:
        cuisine = None

    page_vars = [seamless_link,vendor_id,vend_name,addr,zipcode,phone,price,
                 rating,rating_total,rating_perc,description,reviews,
                 deliv_est,deliv_min,pickup_est,cuisine,estimates_blob]
    a = 'sl_link,vend_id,vend_name,address,zipcode,phone,price'.split(',')
    b = 'rating,rating_total,rating_perc,description'.split(',')
    c = 'reviews,deliv_est,deliv_min,pickup_est,cuisine,estimates_blob'.split(',')
    var_names = a + b + c
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute('drop table if exists tmp')
    pd.DataFrame([page_vars],columns=var_names).to_sql('tmp',engine)

    # upsert to seamless
    cmd = """
        with upd as (
            update seamless s
            set
                vend_name = t.vend_name,
                address = t.address,
                zipcode = t.zipcode,
                phone = t.phone,
                price = t.price,
                rating = t.rating,
                rating_total = t.rating_total,
                rating_perc = t.rating_perc,
                description = t.description,
                reviews = t.reviews,
                deliv_est = t.deliv_est,
                deliv_min = t.deliv_min,
                pickup_est = t.pickup_est,
                cuisine = t.cuisine,
                estimates_blob = t.estimates_blob,
                upd_vend_content = 'now'::timestamp with time zone now
            from tmp t
            where s.vend_id = t.vend_id
            returning t.vend_id vend_id
        )
        insert into seamless ( sl_link,
                               vend_id,
                               vend_name,
                               address,
                               zipcode,
                               phone,
                               price,
                               rating,
                               rating_total,
                               rating_perc,
                               description,
                               reviews,
                               deliv_est,
                               deliv_min,
                               pickup_est,
                               cuisine,
                               estimates_blob,
                               upd_vend_content)
        select
            t.sl_link,
            t.vend_id,
            t.vend_name,
            t.address,
            t.zipcode,
            t.phone,
            t.price,
            t.rating,
            t.rating_total,
            t.rating_perc,
            t.description,
            t.reviews,
            t.deliv_est,
            t.deliv_min,
            t.pickup_est,
            t.cuisine,
            t.estimates_blob,
            'now'::timestamp with time zone now
        from
            tmp t,
            (select array_agg(f.vend_id) upd_vend_ids from upd f) as f1
        where (not upd_vend_ids && array[t.vend_id]
            or upd_vend_ids is null);"""
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute(cmd)
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute("drop table tmp;")
    return

def get_sl_addr_search_results(src):

    br=scraper('firefox').browser
    only_delivery=True

    #------------goto main page, identify PDF-page url, goto PDF-page url
    base_url='http://www.seamless.com/food-delivery/'
    url = 'http://www.seamless.com/'
    br.open_page(url)
    br.window.find_element_by_id("fancybox-close").click()

    d = pd.read_sql(src,engine)

    #i=0
    for i in range(len(d)):
        street,zipcode,gid = d.ix[i,['address','zipcode','gid']].astype(str)
        address = street.title() + ', New York, NY, ' + zipcode
        if only_delivery == True: br.window.find_element_by_id("DeliveryOptionSelection").click()
        sleep(10)
        br.window.find_element_by_name("singleAddressEntry").send_keys(address)
        br.window.find_element_by_name("singleAddressEntry").send_keys(u'\ue007')
        sleep(20)
        if br.window.find_element_by_id("MessageArea").text.find('Your exact address could not be located by our system.') != -1:
            br.window.find_element_by_name("singleAddressEntry").clear()
        elif br.window.find_element_by_class_name("error-header").text.find('Your exact address could not be located by our system.') != -1:
            br.window.find_element_by_name("singleAddressEntry").clear()
        elif br.window.find_element_by_class_name("error-header").text.find("We can't find your address.") != -1:
            br.window.find_element_by_id("fancybox-close").click()
            br.window.find_element_by_name("singleAddressEntry").clear()
        else:
            a=br.window.execute_script('return document.body.scrollHeight;')
            br.window.execute_script("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);")
            sleep(5)
            b=br.window.execute_script('return document.body.scrollHeight;')
            br.window.execute_script("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);")
            sleep(5)
            while a != b:
                a=br.window.execute_script('return document.body.scrollHeight;')
                br.window.execute_script("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);")
                sleep(5)
                b=br.window.execute_script('return document.body.scrollHeight;')
        # --- 2. update pgsql:seamless with address search results
        html = codecs.encode(br.source(),'utf8','ignore')
        z = getTagsByAttr(html, 'div', {'class':'restaurant-name'},contents=False)
        open_res_total = len(z)
        h = pd.Series(map(lambda a: a.a.attrs['href'],z))
        h = h.map(lambda s: base_url + s if s.find('http')==-1 else s)
        t = pd.Series(map(lambda a: a.a.attrs['title'],z))
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute( """drop table if exists tmp;""")
        pd.DataFrame({'sl_link':h,'search_link_blob':t}).to_sql('tmp',engine)

        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute("""
            alter table tmp add column id serial;
            update tmp set id = nextval(pg_get_serial_sequence('tmp','id'));
            alter table tmp add primary key (id);

            alter table tmp add column vend_id bigint;

            update tmp
            set vend_id = substring(sl_link from '[[:punct:]]([[:digit:]]*)[[:punct:]][r]$')::bigint
            where vend_id is null;
            """)
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute("""
                            with upd as (
                                update seamless s
                                set 
                                    search_link_blob = t.search_link_blob,
                                    upd_search_links = now
                                from tmp t
                                left join (select 'now'::timestamp now) as f1 on true is true
                                where s.vend_id = t.vend_id
                                returning s.vend_id vend_id
                            )                   
                            insert into seamless (  
                                sl_link,
                                vend_id,
                                search_link_blob,
                                upd_search_links 
                                )
                            select t.sl_link,t.vend_id,t.search_link_blob,now
                            from 
                                tmp t,
                                (select 'now'::timestamp now) as f1,
                                (select array_agg(f.vend_id) all_vend_id from seamless f) as f2
                            where not all_vend_id @> array[t.vend_id];

                            drop table if exists tmp;
                        """)
        # --- 3. update pgsql:seamless_closed with seamless address search results
        br.window.find_element_by_id("ShowClosedVendorsLink").click()
        sleep(5)
        html = codecs.encode(br.source(),'utf8','ignore')
        z=getTagsByAttr(html, 'div', {'class':'closed1'},contents=False)
        closed_res_total = len(z)
        tmp = map(lambda a: [a.contents[2].replace('\n','').replace('\t','').strip()]+
                             a.span.contents[0].lower().replace('\n','').replace('\t','').replace('open','').strip().split('-'),z)
        T = {'day':dt.datetime.strftime(dt.datetime.now(),'%a').lower()}
        cols = str('vend_name,opens_%(day)s,closes_%(day)s'%T).split(',')
        x = pd.DataFrame(tmp,columns=cols)
        x[cols[1]] = x[cols[1]].map(lambda s: dt.datetime.strftime(dt.datetime.strptime(s,'%I:%M %p'),'%H:%M'))
        x[cols[2]] = x[cols[2]].map(lambda s: dt.datetime.strftime(dt.datetime.strptime(s,'%I:%M %p'),'%H:%M'))
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute( """drop table if exists tmp;""")
        x.to_sql('tmp',engine)
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute("""
            alter table tmp add column id serial;
            update tmp set id = nextval(pg_get_serial_sequence('tmp','id'));
            alter table tmp add primary key (id);
            """)
        # upsert
        check = pd.read_sql('select count(*) cnt from seamless_closed',engine).cnt[0]
        if check == 0:
            conn.set_isolation_level(0)
            cur.execute("""
                            insert into seamless_closed (  
                                vend_name,
                                opens_%(day)s,
                                closes_%(day)s,
                                last_updated )
                            select 
                                t.vend_name,
                                t.opens_%(day)s::time with time zone,
                                t.closes_%(day)s::time with time zone,
                                now
                            from 
                                tmp t,
                                (select 'now'::timestamp with time zone now) as f1;

                            drop table if exists tmp;
                        """%T)
        else:
            conn.set_isolation_level(0)
            cur.execute("""
                            with upd as (
                                update seamless_closed s
                                set 
                                    opens_%(day)s = t.opens_%(day)s::time with time zone,
                                    closes_%(day)s = t.closes_%(day)s::time with time zone,
                                    last_updated = now
                                from 
                                    tmp t,
                                    (select 'now'::timestamp now) as f1
                                where s.vend_name = t.vend_name
                                returning s.vend_name vend_name
                            )                   
                            insert into seamless_closed (  
                                vend_name,
                                opens_%(day)s,
                                closes_%(day)s,
                                last_updated )
                            select 
                                t.vend_name,
                                t.opens_%(day)s::time with time zone,
                                t.closes_%(day)s::time with time zone,
                                now
                            from 
                                tmp t,
                                (select 'now'::timestamp with time zone now) as f1,
                                (select array_agg(f.vend_name) all_vend_names from seamless_closed f) as f2
                            where not all_vend_names @> array[t.vend_name];

                            drop table if exists tmp;
                        """%T)
        # --- 4. update pgsql:scrape_lattice
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute("""  update scrape_lattice
                            set 
                                sl_open_cnt=%s,
                                sl_closed_cnt=%s,
                                sl_updated='now'::timestamp with time zone 
                        where gid=%s"""%(open_res_total,
                                         closed_res_total,
                                         gid))
        # --- 5. put in new address -- repeat
        addresses=br.window.find_element_by_xpath("//select[@id='Address']")
        last_option=len(addresses.find_elements_by_tag_name('option'))-1
        addresses.find_elements_by_tag_name('option')[last_option].click()
        sleep(8)
    br.quit()

# yelp functions

import rauth
from json import dumps as j_dump

CONSUMER_KEY = 'QzH1O3EktEQt89kegeaUxQ'
CONSUMER_SECRET = 'Q_GtZiKGtRvqQSTjGOSgsuogkTE'
TOKEN = '6T7dDEQhf41FA2DIajIDZxsm4RwvBdM9'
TOKEN_SECRET = 'YNaWq3LCjlQu9ir4Ibo-Zp6ELKI'

def yelp_search_api(location,radius_in_meters):
    params = {}
    params["term"] = "restaurant"
    params['location'] = location
    params["radius_filter"] = str(radius_in_meters)
    api_url = 'http://api.yelp.com/v2/search'
    return get_results(params,api_url)

def get_results(params,url):   
    session = rauth.OAuth1Session(
                consumer_key = CONSUMER_KEY
                ,consumer_secret = CONSUMER_SECRET
                ,access_token = TOKEN
                ,access_token_secret = TOKEN_SECRET)
    request = session.get(url,params=params)
    data = request.json()
    session.close()   
    return data

        id serial primary key,
        vend_name text,
        sl_link text,

        opens_mon time with time zone,
        closes_mon time with time zone,

        opens_tue time with time zone,
        closes_tue time with time zone,

        opens_wed time with time zone,
        closes_wed time with time zone,

        opens_thu time with time zone,
        closes_thu time with time zone,

        opens_fri time with time zone,
        closes_fri time with time zone,

        opens_sat time with time zone,
        closes_sat time with time zone,

        opens_sun time with time zone,
        closes_sun time with time zone,
        
        inactive boolean default false,
        inactive_on timestamp with time zone,

        upd_seamless boolean default false,
        last_updated timestamp with time zone
    );
    update seamless_closed set id = nextval(pg_get_serial_sequence('seamless_closed','id'));

    vendor_id = int(z[z[:-2].rfind('.')+1:-2])
    html = codecs.encode(br.source(),'utf8','ignore')
    try:

        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute("""
                    update seamless_closed 
                    set

                        inactive_on = 'now'::timestamp with time zone,
                        sl_link = '%s'
                    where vend_name ilike concat('%%','%s','%%')"""%(sl_link,it[:it.find("'")]))
        continue_processing = False

    if continue_processing == True:
    
        if pd.read_sql("""
                select count(*) c from seamless
                where vend_id = '%(vend_id)s'
                """%{'vend_id':vendor_id},engine).c[0] > 0:
            pass
        
        else:
            try:    br.window.find_element_by_id("fancybox-close").click()
            except: pass

            update_pgsql_with_seamless_page_content(br)
        
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute("""
                update seamless_closed sc
                set 
                    upd_seamless = true,
                    sl_link = '%(sl_link)s'
                from seamless s
                where s.vend_id = '%(v_id)s'
                    """%{'v_id':vendor_id,
                        'sl_link':sl_link})

    conn.set_isolation_level(0)

        update seamless_closed sc

# --------------------------- consolidate overlapping SEAMLESS data
d = pd.read_sql('select * from seamless where vend_cnt>1',engine)
d['upd_vend_content'] = d.upd_vend_content.map(pd.to_datetime)
d['upd_vend_content'] = d.upd_vend_content.map(lambda s: None if str(s).lower()=='nat' else s)
d['upd_search_links'] = d.upd_search_links.map(pd.to_datetime)
d['upd_search_links'] = d.upd_search_links.map(lambda s: None if str(s).lower()=='nat' else s)
d = d.sort(['vend_id','upd_vend_content','upd_search_links'],ascending=[True,False,False]).reset_index(drop=True)

# take latest upd_vend_content updated as primary
# add latest upd_search_links where not null
g = d.groupby('vend_id')
g_keys = g.groups.keys()
f = d.ix[:-1,:]
for it in g_keys:
    vend = g.get_group(it)

    r0 = vend.irow(0,copy=True)
    r1 = vend.irow(1)
    rd1= r1.to_dict()
    skip_vals = ['none','nan']
    for k,v in r1.to_dict().iteritems():
        if skip_vals.count(unicode(v).lower())==0:          # 1. if not a blnk/null value in secondary
            if skip_vals.count(unicode(r0[k]).lower())!=0:  # 2. and if blank/null value in primary
                r0[k] = v                                   # 3. update primary from secondary

    f = f.append(r0,ignore_index=True)

conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute( """drop table if exists tmp;""")
f.to_sql('tmp',engine)
conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""
    alter table tmp add column gid serial primary key;
    update tmp set gid = nextval(pg_get_serial_sequence('tmp','gid'));
    """)

conn.set_isolation_level(0)
cur.execute("""
delete from seamless s
using (select array_agg(t.vend_id) A from tmp t) as f1
where array[s.vend_id] && A;
""")


cmd="""
create table tmp2 as
select gid,upd_search_links from tmp
where upd_search_links!='None';

update tmp set upd_search_links_tmp = null;

update tmp t set upd_search_links_tmp = t2.upd_search_links::timestamp with time zone
from tmp2 t2
where t2.gid = t.gid;

drop table tmp2;

create table tmp2 as
select gid,upd_vend_content from tmp
where upd_vend_content!='None';

update tmp set upd_vend_content_tmp = null;

update tmp t set upd_vend_content_tmp = t2.upd_vend_content::timestamp with time zone
from tmp2 t2
where t2.gid = t.gid;

drop table tmp2;

alter table tmp drop column upd_search_links;
alter table tmp drop column upd_vend_content;
alter table tmp rename column upd_search_links_tmp to upd_search_links;
alter table tmp rename column upd_vend_content_tmp to upd_vend_content;
"""
# after removing all NaN using:
#      update tmp set rating_perc = null where rating_perc::text='NaN'
# ...
cmd="""
insert into seamless (  sl_link,
                        vend_id,
                        vend_name,

# create table yelp
cmd="""

CREATE TABLE yelp
(
  id serial primary key,
  yelp_id text,
  vend_name text,
  phone integer,
  address text,
  city text,
  state_code text,
  postal_code integer,
  display_phone text,
  is_claimed boolean,
  is_closed boolean,
  menu_date_updated text,
  menu_provider text,
  rating double precision,
  review_count integer,
  categories text,
  url text,
  latitude double precision,
  longitude double precision,
  geo_accuracy double precision

);


"""

%sql postgres@routing $cmd

# 0. get results from yelp address search and update pgsql

import sys
reload(sys)
sys.setdefaultencoding('UTF8')

try:
    
#     s = pd.read_sql(""" select gid,address,zipcode from scrape_lattice
#                         where yelp_updated is null
#                         or age('now'::timestamp with time zone,yelp_updated) > interval '1 day'
#                     """,engine)
    s = pd.read_sql(""" select gid,address,zipcode from scrape_lattice where yelp_updated > '2014-11-24 18:22:59.045361-05'::timestamp with time zone;
                    """,engine)
    
    p = map(lambda s: str(s[0].title()+', New York, NY '+str(s[1])),zip(s.address,s.zipcode))

    
    br=scraper('phantom').browser
    #!pkill -f firefox
    # br=scraper('firefox').browser
    
    
    d_cols = ['vend_name','url','phone']
    base_url='http://www.yelp.com'
    for i in range(len(p)):
        gid = s.ix[i,'gid']
        search_addr = p[i]

        url = base_url+'/search?find_desc='+safe_url('restaurant')+'&find_loc='+safe_url(search_addr)
        br.open_page(url)

        if getTagsByAttr(br.source(), 'div', {'class':'no-results'},contents=False): pass
        else:
            html = codecs.encode(br.source(),'utf8','ignore')
            if html.find('ylist')==-1:
                res_num = 0
                conn.set_isolation_level(0)
                cur.execute("""  update scrape_lattice
                                    set yelp_cnt=%s,
                                    yelp_updated='now'::timestamp with time zone 
                                where gid=%s
                           """%(str(res_num),gid))
            else:
                a = getTagsByAttr(html, 'span', {'class':'pagination-results-window'},contents=True)
                res_num = int(re_findall(r'\d+', str(a[a.find('of')+3:]))[0])
                conn.set_isolation_level(0)
                cur.execute("""  update scrape_lattice
                                    set yelp_cnt=%s,
                                    yelp_updated='now'::timestamp with time zone 
                                 where gid=%s
                           """%(str(res_num),gid))
                d = pd.DataFrame(columns=d_cols)
                first_page,last_page = True,False

                while last_page == False:

                    a = getTagsByAttr(html, 'ul', {'class':'ylist ylist-bordered search-results'},contents=False)
                    names = a[0].findAll('a',attrs={'class':'biz-name'})
                    names_proper = map(lambda s: str(s.contents[0]).replace('\xe2\x80\x99',"'")
                                        if len(s.contents)>0 else '',names)
                    links = map(lambda s: base_url+str(s.attrs['href']),names)
                    phones = a[0].findAll('span',attrs={'class':'biz-phone'})
                    phones_proper = map(lambda s: ''.join(re_findall(r'\d+', str(s))),phones)

                    z = {'vend_name':pd.Series(names_proper),
                         'url':pd.Series(links),
                         'phone':pd.Series(phones_proper)}
                    d = d.append(pd.DataFrame(data=z,columns=d_cols),ignore_index=True)        

                    next_page = getSoup(html).findAll('a', {'class':'page-option prev-next'})
                    if first_page==True and len(next_page)==1:
                        next_page_link = base_url + next_page[0].attrs['href']
                        br.open_page(next_page_link)
                        html = codecs.encode(br.source(),'utf8','ignore')
                        first_page = False
                    elif len(next_page)==2:
                        next_page_link = base_url + next_page[1].attrs['href']
                        br.open_page(next_page_link)
                        html = codecs.encode(br.source(),'utf8','ignore')
                    else:
                        last_page = True
                        break

                    # upsert to yelp
                    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
                    cur.execute('drop table if exists tmp')
                    d['id'] = d.url.map(lambda s: s[s.find('/biz/')+5:])
                    d['phone_as_text'] = d.phone.map(str)
                    d.to_sql('tmp',engine)

                    cmd = """
                        with upd as (
                            update yelp y
                            set
                                id = t.id,
                                vend_name = t.vend_name,
                                url = t.url,
                                phone_as_text = t.phone_as_text,
                                upd_search_links = 'now'::timestamp with time zone
                            from tmp t
                            where y.url = t.url
                            returning t.url url
                        )
                        insert into yelp ( id,
                                           vend_name,
                                           url,
                                           phone_as_text,
                                           upd_search_links)
                        select
                            t.id,
                            t.vend_name,
                            t.url,
                            t.phone_as_text,
                            'now'::timestamp with time zone
                        from
                            tmp t,
                            (select array_agg(f.url) upd_vend_urls from upd f) as f2
                        where (not upd_vend_urls && array[t.url]
                            or upd_vend_urls is null);"""
                    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
                    cur.execute(cmd)
                    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
                    cur.execute("""drop table tmp;""")
except:
    pass

# 1. get results from yelp Search API with scape lattice addresses and update pgsql -- worked 2014.11.17

# s = pd.read_sql(""" select gid,address,zipcode from scrape_lattice
#                     where yelp_updated is null
#                     or age('now'::timestamp with time zone,yelp_updated) > interval '1 day'
#                 """,engine)

s = pd.read_sql(""" select gid,address,zipcode from scrape_lattice
                    where yelp_updated<='2014-11-24 18:21:07.012204-05:00'::timestamp with time zone;
                """,engine)

p = map(lambda s: str(s[0].title()+', New York, NY '+str(s[1])),zip(s.address,s.zipcode))

# (from scrape_lattice creation function) [ADD TO SETTINGS DB]
pt_buff_in_miles = 0.2
lattice_table_name = 'scrape_lattice'
# 1 miles = 1609.34 meters
radius_in_meters = 1600 * pt_buff_in_miles

for i in range(len(p)):
    gid = s.ix[i,'gid']
    search_addr = p[i]
    d = yelp_search_api(search_addr,radius_in_meters)
    # try:
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute("""  update scrape_lattice
                            set yelp_cnt=%s,
                            yelp_updated='now'::timestamp with time zone 
                        where gid=%s
                   """%(d['total'],gid))
    df = pd.read_json(j_dump(d['businesses']))

    if len(df)>0:
        all_res_cols = df.columns.tolist()
        df['vend_name'] = df.name
        if all_res_cols.count('phone')>0:
            df['phone'] = df.phone.map(lambda s: int(s) if str(s)[0].isdigit() else None)
        else:
            df['phone'] = None
        df['address'] = df.location.map(lambda s:
                                        None if len(s['address'])==0
                                        else s['address'][0])
        df['display_address'] = df.location.map(lambda s:
                                        None if s.keys().count('display_address')==0
                                        else ','.join(s['display_address']))
        df['neighborhoods'] = df.location.map(lambda s:
                                        None if s.keys().count('neighborhoods')==0
                                        else s['neighborhoods'][0])
        df['city'] = df.location.map(lambda s:
                                     None if s.keys().count('city')==0
                                     else s['city'])
        df['state_code'] = df.location.map(lambda s:
                                           None if s.keys().count('state_code')==0
                                           else s['state_code'])        
        df['postal_code'] = df.location.map(lambda s: 
                                            None if s.keys().count('postal_code')==0
                                            else int(s['postal_code']))
        df['latitude'] = df.location.map(lambda s:
                                           None if (s.keys().count('coordinate')==0 or 
                                                    s['coordinate'].keys().count('latitude')==0)
                                           else s['coordinate']['latitude'])
        df['longitude'] = df.location.map(lambda s:
                                           None if (s.keys().count('coordinate')==0 or 
                                                    s['coordinate'].keys().count('longitude')==0)
                                           else s['coordinate']['longitude'])
        df['geo_accuracy'] = df.location.map(lambda s: 
                                             None if s.keys().count('geo_accuracy')==0
                                             else int(s['geo_accuracy']))
        if df.columns.tolist().count('menu_date_updated')==0:
            df['menu_date_updated'] = None
        else:
            df['menu_date_updated'] = df.menu_date_updated.map(lambda x:
                None if str(x)[0].isdigit()==False
                else datetime.fromtimestamp(  int(x)  ).strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') 
                                                                )
        df = df.ix[:,[   'id',
                         'vend_name',
                         'phone',
                         'address',
                         'display_address',
                         'neighborhoods',
                         'city',
                         'state_code',
                         'postal_code',
                         'display_phone',        
                         'is_claimed',
                         'is_closed',
                         'menu_date_updated',
                         'menu_provider',
                         'rating',
                         'review_count',
                         'categories',
                         'url',
                         'latitude',
                         'longitude',
                         'geo_accuracy']]

        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute( """drop table if exists tmp;""")
        df.to_sql('tmp',engine)

        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute("""

            alter table tmp add column gid serial primary key;
            update tmp set gid = nextval(pg_get_serial_sequence('tmp','gid'));

            update tmp set phone = null where phone::text = 'NaN';
            update tmp set postal_code = null where postal_code::text = 'NaN';

            """)

        # upsert 'tmp' to 'yelp'
        cmd="""
        with upd as (
            update yelp y
            set
                id = t.id,
                vend_name = t.vend_name,
                phone = t.phone::bigint,
                address = t.address,
                display_address = t.display_address,
                neighborhoods = t.neighborhoods,
                city = t.city,
                state_code = t.state_code,
                postal_code = t.postal_code::bigint,
                display_phone = t.display_phone,
                is_claimed = t.is_claimed,
                is_closed = t.is_closed,
                menu_date_updated = t.menu_date_updated,
                menu_provider = t.menu_provider,
                rating = t.rating,
                review_count = t.review_count,
                categories = t.categories,
                url = t.url,
                latitude = t.latitude,
                longitude = t.longitude,
                geo_accuracy = t.geo_accuracy,
                last_api_update = 'now'::timestamp with time zone
            from tmp t
            where y.id = t.id
            returning t.id id
        )
        insert into yelp (  id,
                            vend_name,
                            phone,
                            address,
                            display_address,
                            neighborhoods,
                            city,
                            state_code,
                            postal_code,
                            display_phone,
                            is_claimed,
                            is_closed,
                            menu_date_updated,
                            menu_provider,
                            rating,
                            review_count,
                            categories,
                            url,
                            latitude,
                            longitude,
                            geo_accuracy,
                            last_api_update
                        )
        select
            t.id,
            t.vend_name,
            t.phone::bigint,
            t.address,
            t.display_address,
            t.neighborhoods,
            t.city,
            t.state_code,
            t.postal_code::bigint,
            t.display_phone,
            t.is_claimed,
            t.is_closed,
            t.menu_date_updated,
            t.menu_provider,
            t.rating,
            t.review_count,
            t.categories,
            t.url,
            t.latitude,
            t.longitude,
            t.geo_accuracy,
            'now'::timestamp with time zone
        from
            tmp t,
            (select array_agg(f.id) upd_ids from upd f) as f1
        where (not upd_ids && array[t.id]
            or upd_ids is null);


        drop table tmp;

        """
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute(cmd)

print 'done!'

# 2. use yelp.url to get hours from each page and update pgsql -- worked 2014.11.03 

# d = pd.read_sql(""" select gid,url from yelp
#                     where hours_updated is null
#                     or age(hours_updated,'now'::timestamp with time zone) > interval '1 day'
#                 """,engine)
d = pd.read_sql(""" select gid,url from yelp
                    where hours_updated is null
                """,engine)
                        
y_links = d.url.tolist()
br=scraper('phantom').browser
# !pkill -f firefox
# br=scraper('firefox').browser

for it in y_links:
    br.open_page(it)
    html = codecs.encode(br.source(),'utf8','ignore')

    # extract yelp page data
    vend_data = {'url':it}

    # biz info
    try:
        s=getSoup(html).find('h3',text='More business info').find_parent()
        t=s.find('div', {'class':'short-def-list'},contents=False)
        d_keys=map(lambda x: str(x.get_text().strip('\n ')),t.findAll('dt'))
        d_vals=map(lambda x: str(x.get_text().strip('\n ')),t.findAll('dd'))
        d = dict(zip(d_keys,d_vals))
        vend_data.update({'extra_info':str(d).replace("'",'"')})
    except:
        vend_data.update({'extra_info':None})

    # hours info
    t=getTagsByAttr(html, 'table', {'class':'table table-simple hours-table'},contents=False)
    if len(t)!=0:
        t=t[0]
        days = map(lambda s: str(s.get_text()),t.findAll('th',attrs={'scope':'row'}))
        hours = map(lambda s: str(s.get_text().strip('\n ')),t.findAll('td',attrs={'class':''}))
        h = str(zip(days,hours)).replace("'",'"')
        vend_data.update({'hours':h})
    else:
        vend_data.update({'hours':None})

    # biz website
    t=getTagsByAttr(html, 'div', {'class':'biz-website'},contents=False)
    if len(t)!=0:
        t = t[0].a.attrs['href']
        s =t.find('url=')+4
        e = t.find('&',s)
        biz_website = str(unquote(t[s:e]))
        vend_data.update({'website':biz_website})
    else:
        vend_data.update({'website':None})

    # non-yelp menu link
    t=getTagsByAttr(html, 'a', {'class':'i-wrap ig-wrap-common i-external-link-common-wrap ig-wrap-common-r external-menu'},contents=False)
    if len(t)!=0:
        t = t[0].attrs['href']
        s = t.find('url=')+4
        biz_menu_page = str(unquote(t[s:]))
        vend_data.update({'menu_page':biz_menu_page.replace("'","''")})
    else:
        vend_data.update({'menu_page':None})

    # price range
    try:
        price_range = str(getTagsByAttr(html, 'dd', {'class':'nowrap price-description'},contents=False)[0].get_text().strip('\n $'))
        vend_data.update({'price_range':price_range})
    except:
        vend_data.update({'price_range':None})

    # online ordering?
    t=getTagsByAttr(html, 'div', {'data-ro-mode-action':'place an order'},contents=False) # null return
    online_ordering = len(t)!=0
    #t=getTagsByAttr(html, 'div', {'class':'island platform yform js-platform no-js-hidden'},contents=False)
    vend_data.update({'online_ordering':online_ordering})

    # push to pgsql
    cmd = """
    update yelp set 
        extra_info = '%(extra_info)s',
        hours = '%(hours)s',
        hours_updated = 'now'::timestamp with time zone,
        menu_page = '%(menu_page)s',
        online_ordering=%(online_ordering)s,
        price_range='%(price_range)s',
        website = '%(website)s'
    where url = '%(url)s'

    """%(vend_data)
    conn.set_isolation_level(0)
    cur.execute(cmd)

print 'done!'
beep()

def add_new_vendor_info(g='Parsed PDF'):
    parties = g[ ((115<=g.top)&(g.top<=165)) ]
    c = g[ ((520<=g.left)&(g.left<=530)) ].sort('top')
    c = c.text.map(lambda s: unicode(s, errors='ignore')).tolist()
    vend_cols = ['vend_name','vend_addr','vend_tel']
    T = dict(zip(vend_cols,[c[0].strip(),c[1].strip()+', '+c[2].strip(),re_sub(r'[\W_]+', '', c[3])]))
    v_cnt = pd.read_sql("select count(*) c from aprinto_vendor where vend_tel = '%(vend_tel)s'"%T,engine).c[0]
    if v_cnt==0:
        conn.set_isolation_level(0)
        cur.execute("""
            insert into aprinto_vendor(created,vend_name,vend_addr,vend_tel)
            VALUES ('now'::timestamp with time zone,'%(vend_name)s','%(vend_addr)s','%(vend_tel)s')"""%T)
    return

def parse_pdf_from_admin(pdf):
    """
    A UUID is generated on each install of the Aporo printer driver.  Aprinto only processes PDFs from
    authenticated printer drivers, which have either admin or vendor credentials.  All other printer 
    drivers are considered "potential_clients."
    
    One way to authenticate users is:
    
        1. Print a completed contract from a printer driver registered with admin credentials.
        2. Parse PDF, get client info from contract, and update DB.
        3. Wait for same PDF from "potential_client"
        
    """
    x = soup(pdf).findAll('page')
    cols = ['page','font','top','left','width','height','text']
    g = pd_DataFrame(columns=cols)
    for pg in x:
        pg = x[0]
        idx = x.index(pg)+1
        pg = str(pg)
        line_iter = re_findall(r'(<text.*?</text>)',pg)

        for it in line_iter:
            a = ['page']+re_findall('([a-zA-Z]+)+\=', it)+['text']
            text_attrs = it[5:it.find('>')].strip()
            text_contents = str(soup(it).text)
            b = [idx]+map(lambda s: int(s),re_findall('[0-9]+', text_attrs))+[text_contents]
            if text_contents.strip() != '':
                g = g.append(dict(zip(a,b)),ignore_index=True)

    chk_trial_period   =  g.sort('top').text.str.contains('SERVICE AGREEMENT – Trial Period').tolist().count(True)!=0
    if chk_trial_period:  add_new_vendor_info(g)

    return True

# Functions
def post_json(all_data,p_url,show_post=False,show_resp=False):

    if show_post == True:
        print '\t\t\tJSON Posted:\n'
        print json.dumps(all_data, indent=4, sort_keys=True)

    json_data = json.dumps(all_data)
    headers = {'Content-type': 'application/json'}
    req = Request(p_url, json_data, headers)
    f = urlopen(req)
    print f
    response = f.read()
    f.close()

    if show_resp == True:
        try:
            parsed = json.loads(response)
            print '\t\t\tServer Response:\n'
            print json.dumps(parsed, indent=4, sort_keys=True)
        except:
            print '\nNON-JSON RESPONE\n\n\t\t\tServer Response:\n'
            print response

    return response

def check(post_action='',show_info=False,show_post=False,show_resp=False):
    p_url = BASE_URL+'/api/check/'
    if show_info == True: print '\n\t\tTEST #1: printer driver check-in',post_action,'\n\t\t\tURL:',p_url
    guid = str(get_guid())
    data = [{
              'pdf_id' : guid,
              'printer_id' : 'printer_id1',
#               'machine_id' : '12c61d88-5d0c-44af-a5fc-734f6327e1ec',
#               'machine_id' : 'admin1',
                'machine_id' : 'vendor1',
              'application_name' : 'application_name1',
              'doc_name' : 'test_unit_1'
            }]

    resp = post_json(data,p_url,show_post,show_resp)
    if show_info == True: print '\n\t\t\t--> #1 SUCCESS\n'
    return guid

def upload_pdf(guid,uploadfile,upload_file_url,show_info=False,show_post=False,show_resp=False):
    if show_info == True: print '\t\tTEST #2: upload_pdf -->',uploadfile,'\n\n\t\t\tURL:',upload_file_url
    opener = register_openers()

    params = {'local_document': open(uploadfile,'rb'),
              'pdf_id' : guid}

    datagen, headers = multipart_encode(params)
    R = Request(upload_file_url, datagen, headers)

    if show_resp == True:
        print '\n\n\t\t\tURL Post Request:'
        print '\n\t\t\t\tHeaders:'
        print '\n\t\t\t\t\t',R.headers,'\n'
        print '\n\t\t\t\tParams:'
        print '\n\t\t\t\t\t',params,'\n'
        print '\t\t\t\tTotal Size:'
        print '\n\t\t\t\t\t',R.data.total,'\n'

    response = opener.open(R)

    if show_post == True:
        print '\n\t\t\tServer Response:'
        print '\n\t\t\t\t',response.read(),'\n'

    if show_info == True: print '\n\t\t\t--> #2 SUCCESS\n'
    return True

def upload_test(uploadfile,upload_file_url,show_info=False):
    guid = check(post_action='',show_info=show_info,show_post=show_info,show_resp=show_info)
    upload_pdf(guid,uploadfile,upload_file_url,show_info=show_info,show_post=show_info,show_resp=show_info)
    return True

import logging
import optparse

LOGGING_LEVELS = {'critical': logging.CRITICAL,
                  'error': logging.ERROR,
                  'warning': logging.WARNING,
                  'info': logging.INFO,
                  'debug': logging.DEBUG}

def main():
  parser = optparse.OptionParser()
  parser.add_option('-l', '--logging-level', help='Logging level')
  parser.add_option('-f', '--logging-file', help='Logging file name')
  (options, args) = parser.parse_args()
  logging_level = LOGGING_LEVELS.get(options.logging_level, logging.NOTSET)
  logging.basicConfig(level=logging_level, filename=options.logging_file,
                      format='%(asctime)s %(levelname)s: %(message)s',
                      datefmt='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')

  # Your program goes here.
  # You can access command-line arguments using the args variable.

if __name__ == '__main__':
  main()

how to use the above:

By default, the logging module prints critical, error and warning messages. To change this so that all levels are printed, use:

$ ./your-program.py --logging=debug To send log messages to a file called debug.log, use:

$ ./your-program.py --logging-level=debug --logging-file=debug.log

from pyproj import Proj, transform

from urllib2 import urlopen
def get_epsg(check_code):
    x= 'http://www.spatialreference.org/ref/esri/%s/proj4/' % check_code
    return urlopen(x).read()
# inProj = Proj('+proj=lcc +lat_1=40.66666666666666 +lat_2=41.03333333333333 +lat_0=40.16666666666666 +lon_0=-74 +x_0=300000 +y_0=0 +datum=NAD83 +units=us-ft +no_defs')

# Converting from lion to WGS 84
# inProj = Proj(get_epsg('102718'))
# outProj = Proj(init='epsg:4326')

# Converting from WGS84 to lion
inProj = Proj(init='epsg:4326')
outProj = Proj(get_epsg('102718'))
x1,y1 = -73.98468,40.74531

x2,y2 = transform(inProj,outProj,x1,y1)
print x2,y2
